  "time_ut": 1659431747,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0da0\u0dd3\u0db1 \u0db1\u0dde\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dc0 \u0d91\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1\u0dda \u0d89\u0db1\u0dca\u0db0\u0db1 \u0dbd\u0db6\u0dcf\u0d9c\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The Chinese ship is coming to get fuel",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Minister of Transport, Highways and Mass Media, Dr. Bandula Gunawardena said that Foreign Minister Ali Sabri informed the President and the Cabinet that a scheduled Chinese research ship will arrive at Hambantota Port only to fulfill fuel and other needs.",
        "The Minister also mentioned that Foreign Minister Ali Sabri informed that the ship is not coming for any other purpose.",
        "The minister said this while addressing the press conference to announce the cabinet decisions held today (2) at the Government Information Department.",
        "The minister also said that President Ranil Wickramasinghe said that he would work with friendly countries including India and China to help Sri Lanka in difficult times."
      ],
